item.title: Fateh Review: The No-Nonsense, Unabashed And Ultra-Violent Film Is Surprisingly Watchable - NDTV Movies
item.description:
Fateh Review: The No-Nonsense, Unabashed And Ultra-Violent Film Is Surprisingly Watchable

Publication Date: New Delhi

An ex-special ops agent embarks on a violent rampage to take down cyber criminals behind a fraudulent loan operation. Actor Sonu Sood makes his writing and directing debut with a film that is unapologetically violent and dynamic.

  • The film opens with an intense confrontation where the protagonist, Fateh Singh, takes control by resorting to extreme violence.
  • Fateh utilizes a variety of weapons in his mission against a network of cyber criminals, showcasing high body counts reminiscent of other action-packed films.
  • The narrative includes a social purpose, focusing on the impact of a scam targeting financially vulnerable individuals.
  • Despite the relentless violence, the film offers minimal mystery as the antagonist's identity is revealed early on.
  • Sonu Sood's performance resonates with the film's gritty tone, although other characters struggle to stand out in the chaos.
“Fateh is marked by dizzying momentum if not sustained clarity.”

In conclusion, while Fateh may be overwhelming with its sheer brutality, it remains a captivating watch for those who appreciate action-packed narratives.

item.title: Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah's Gurucharan Singh 'Critical': 'Has Not Eaten Food For 19 Days' - News18
item.description:
Gurucharan Singh from Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah in Critical Condition After 19 Days Without Food

Date: January 10, 2025 Source: News18

Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah actor Gurucharan Singh is currently hospitalized and in critical condition after not eating for 19 days.

  • His friend Bhakti Soni expressed concern over Singh's health, stating he has not taken any food or water.
  • During their last conversation, Singh indicated uncertainty about his survival.
  • He recently shared a video on Instagram, thanking everyone for their support and acknowledging his serious health condition.
  • Gurucharan Singh is well-known for his role as Roshan Singh Sodhi on the show.
“He hasn’t eaten food or drunk water for 19 days. Because of that, he fell unconscious and was quickly rushed to the hospital.” - Bhakti Soni

In conclusion, Singh’s situation is dire, and he is under medical care while his friends and family express their utmost concern over his well-being.

item.title: Ajith Kumar reveals he will not sign any film until the race season is over: 'I plan to pursue motorsport - TOI Etimes
item.description:
Ajith Kumar reveals he will not sign any film until the race season is over: 'I plan to pursue motorsports'

Publication Date: Not specified Source: Times of India

Ajith Kumar, the popular actor, has announced that he will focus on his motorsport career and will not be signing new films until the racing season is complete. He recently suffered an injury during his practice but remains committed to the upcoming 24H Dubai car race.

  • Ajith is teaming up with Mathieu Detry, Fabian Duffieux, and Cameron McLeod for the race.
  • The race is scheduled for January 11-12.
  • He plans to pursue motorsports not just as a driver but as a team owner.
  • Ajith intends to act in films between October and March, before the racing season starts.
  • He has two major films coming in 2025, including 'Good Bad Ugly' on April 10.
“I plan to pursue motorsports, not just as a driver but as a team owner as well. Until the racing season is on, I won’t be signing any films.”

Ajith's commitment to both film and racing highlights his dedication to his dual passions, ensuring he can give his all to both pursuits.

item.title: Game Changer movie leaked online: Ram Charan, Kiara Advani-starrer becomes the victim of piracy within hours of release - The Indian Express
item.description:
Game Changer movie leaked online: Ram Charan, Kiara Advani-starrer becomes the victim of piracy within hours of release

Date: January 10, 2025 | Source: Indian Express

The much-anticipated film Game Changer, featuring Ram Charan and Kiara Advani, was leaked online shortly after its release, raising concerns about piracy.

  • The film was released on January 10, 2025, but unauthorized copies began circulating within hours.
  • Pirated versions are reportedly available on several piracy websites, including Tamilrockers and Movierulz.
  • Fans reacted positively to the film, praising performances and specific scenes despite mixed reviews.
  • Three songs were reportedly edited out due to technical difficulties, with plans to add them back shortly.
  • The film has a reported budget of Rs 450 crore, making it one of the most expensive Tollywood films.
“#GameChanger is a crisp, fast-paced, & heartfelt entertainer. It boldly delves into themes of power dynamics & their ties to systemic injustices.”

This incident underscores the ongoing issue of film piracy, impacting the film industry significantly.

item.title: Game Changer box office collection day 1 early report: Ram Charan-starrer likely to cross Rs 30 crore mark - The Indian Express
item.description:
Game Changer Box Office Collection Day 1 Early Report

Date: January 10, 2025 Source: Indian Express

Introduction: After five years of anticipation, Game Changer, starring Ram Charan and Kiara Advani, premiered on January 10 and garnered over Rs 32.41 crore by 9 PM on its opening day, signaling a strong box office performance.

  • The film has approximately 7500 shows across India, with the Telugu version leading with 3863 shows.
  • It earned Rs 43.55 crore in advance bookings, with Andhra Pradesh contributing the highest gross.
  • The release impacted the sales of Pushpa 2 tickets, which saw a significant decline.
  • Mixed reviews have been noted, with an average rating of 2.5 from SCREEN.
“Game Changer is essentially a lot of nice segments that are stitched together in the hope that it would make a good film.” - Avinash Ramachandran, SCREEN

Conclusion: Game Changer's debut reflects both the potential of Ram Charan’s star power and the challenges of mixed reviews, positioning it as a key player in the competitive box office landscape.
